BMW Plans New Assembly Plant in Brazil, Automobilwoche Reports

-- B y   S h e e n a g h   M a t t h e w s
-- 
2011-08-20T11:22:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-20/bmw-plans-new-assembly-plant-in-brazil-automobilwoche-reports.html
Bayerische Motoren Werke AG (BMW)  plans to
build an assembly plant in Brazil to meet global demand,
 Automobilwoche reported , without saying where it got the
information.  The list of potential sites for the factory has been
narrowed to two, one of which is close to  Sao Paulo , and a final
decision will be made in October, the German magazine said. The
carmaker is considering expansion of its plants in Russia and
India, Automobilwoche said.  BMW also plans its own wind-power plant with four windmills
to help power a factory in the German city of Leipzig, the
magazine reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sheenagh Matthews in Frankfurt at 
 smatthews6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at   bkammel@bloomberg.net . 